description:
Last issue in its current format - from issue 423 there are new stories, all in full colour for the first time.

This is also the last issue that Max (from The Thirteenth Floor stories) edits the comic.

Loner (the last surviving story from Wildcat) reaches its conclusion this issue after 48 episodes and there's the final reprinted chapter of the World War One story - Charley's War.

Cover: newstand style announcement for next issues changes

  • Computer Warrior - Ghouls 'n' Ghosts (part 8 - final part) (John Wagner - Mike Dorey)
  • Toys of Doom (part 26 - double sized final episode)
  • Loner (part 48- final part) (art: Eric Bradbury)
  • Dan Dare - Cadets (part 6 - final part) (art: Keith Page)
  • Storm Force (part 120- final part) (James Nicholas - Vanyo)
  • Charley's War (Pat Mills - Joe Colquhoun)
  • Rat-Trap (part 27 - final part)

New look issue (more colour and glossy paper) and all new stories. There are five stories (instead of the previous seven), but Dan Dare and Computer Warrior both increase to four pages in length.

Cover: David Pugh (Dan Dare)

  • Dan Dare - Nightmare Machines (part 1) (Tom Tully - David Pugh)
  • Computer Warrior - Black Tiger (prologue) (John Wagner - Mike Dorey)
  • The Eagle One-Off - Mutants (David Robinson - Alan Burrows)
  • Ghostworld (part 1) (James Nicholas - Eric Bradbury)
  • Dark Angels (part 1) (Tom Tully - Solano Lopez)

No Dark Angels this issue, instead there are two biography pages for the characters.

Cover: David Pugh (Dan Dare)

  • Dan Dare - Nightmare Machines (part 2) (Tom Tully - David Pugh)
  • The Eagle One-Off - Experiments in Terror (David Robinson - Alan Burrows)
  • Computer Warrior - Black Tiger (part 1) (John Wagner - Mike Dorey)
  • Ghostworld (part 2) (James Nicholas - Eric Bradbury)
  • Dark Angels - character information (Tom Tully - Solano Lopez)

This issue concludes the mini-series. Mars has changed, but Quaid finds that other things remain the same. He is still running and fighting for his life. The fate of Mars is still in his hands. Quaid will now have to fight in an epic struggle to save the day. All of the mysteries are unveiled.

Following the events in the SILENT ONES, James Jensen is at a crossroads in history. India has gained a new freedom movement. Proponents of armed revolution stand on one side while messiah Mahatma Gandhi preaches non-violence on the other. As the British Empire fights for control of India, the Sadhu is locked in the middle, where his actions can sway fate.

James Jenson, A British soldier whose family is brutally murdered by a corrupt superior officer, seeks refuge with the Indian mystics known as Sadhus. Years later, now trained in their supernatural arts, Jenson must decide whether to use his newfound powers for inner peace as they are intended, or for revenge against the people who murdered his family.

Collects Sadhu Issues #1-8.
name: Volume 1: When Realities Collide

description:
From the publisher:

Frankfurt - sometime in the far-ish future. Earth is recovering from a brief war against Lunar Separatists.

Following a brutal car wreck, Jan has been projected into an old lunar-made body while his body recovers in the hospital. He soon discovers that similar model lunar bodies are being used in terrorist attacks by a rogue group of Lunar Separatists, and turns to his best friend Anders for help.

What they discover goes deeper than Jan could have ever imagined.
name: Jan's Atomic Heart

description: How do Deadpool and Bob, the two most wanted terrorists in the world, spend their holiday break? By faking their own deaths, breaking into CIA headquarters, hunting down internet-porn-peddling jihadists and causing a riot in an insane asylum, of course!
name: Deadpool MAX-Mas Special

volume.name: Marge's Little Lulu and Tubby at Summer Camp

description:
Collecting The Sadhu: The Silent Ones #1-5:

In the 19th century, when the sun did not dare set on the British Empire, James Jensen went to India as a soldier in the Her Majesty's Army. Losing his family to betrayal and violence, Jensen became a SADHU, a True Warrior who must embrace the spiritual path to salvation. Now an emptiness rules James Jensen's heart, and he wanders aimlessly. His travels bring him to the Kumbh Mela, a truly epic gathering of mystics, where deadly enemies and shadowy allies lie in wait. But even that's not the biggest surprise, as James learns that a loved one might indeed still live.

Volume 2 collects issues #1-5 of The Sadhu: The Silent Ones.
name: Volume 2: The Silent Ones

description: Previously James Jensen, The Sadhu, joined the rebels to rid India of tyranny. Now he enters Limbo once again to find a better alternate reality and merge it with his own reality. However the task proves less than easy, as James explores the endless possibilities of various worlds. He finally arrives at one that may be too much to handle.
James Jensen continues at the heart of the struggle between armed revolution and non-violence. The British Empire grows even more desperate to maintain control.

Chapter Listing

  • Chapter 1 - Late Spring in Vienna
  • Chapter 2 - Jeanne D'Arc in Hell
  • Chapter 3 - The Beautiful Goddess of War Nike of Samothrace
  • Chapter 4 - The Bewitching Queen of Versailles
  • Chapter 5 - The Demon of the Little Bighorn
name: Vol. 1

description: Christina and her rowdy girlfriends go to the Daytona Bike Week motorcycle rally and sneak into a nightclub to see a heavy metal band. After taking a hit of the supernatural drug known as Stairway to Heaven, Christina and Trish start seeing ghosts and are stalked by a headless Hell's Angel on a motorcycle who collects the souls of sinners.
It is also no. 6 of "A giant comic" series.
